Installation of Windows Server Backup Tool:

The Windows Server Backup tool is a built-in backup utility found in Windows server operating systems. It can be used for all servers.

To install:
Navigate to DC -> add roles and features -> features -> windows server backup -> install.

Preparation Before Backing Up
- Check if there is replication between domain controllers.

Backing Up Data
- Use the Windows Server Backup tool.
- If you want to schedule backups at specific intervals, use the Backup Schedule feature.
- For backing up only AD, use the System State backup option.

For a comprehensive backup, including everything under the C drive, system requirements, and necessary components for Domain Controller and AD, use the Bare Metal Recovery option.